title: Alaska Airlines continues to grow Seattle hub
text:
Alaska Airlines continues to grow Seattle hub   02, 2015 eTN   
SEATTLE, WA - Alaska Airlines is expanding its Seattle hub today with the start of new service from the Emerald City to Raleigh/Durham, North Carolina. Raleigh is the sixth new city the carrier has added this year, following last month's start of service from Seattle to Nashville and New York City's JFK. 
Summary of new Seattle-Raleigh/Durham service: 
Start date City pair Departs Arrives Frequency Oct. 1 Seattle-Raleigh/Durham 8:40 a.m. 4:50 p.m. Daily Oct. 1 Raleigh/Durham-Seattle 5:50 p.m. 9 p.m. Daily 
Flights will be operated by fuel-efficient Next Generation 737 aircraft. Onboard, customers will get to enjoy more of what they love with free exclusive programming streamed to their own devices, Pacific Northwest-inspired food and beverages and power outlets at each seat.
